# GitHub Linguist hints.
#
# Rush is a Rust project. The legacy .NET Rush interpreter under
# dotnet/ (being retired per #267 Phase 6) is still present for
# reference during the migration, but it's 30k+ LOC of C# that
# drowns out the Rust code when GitHub counts bytes for "primary
# language" detection.
#
# Mark the legacy tree as vendored so it's excluded from language
# stats. The active PowerShell bridge under dotnet/rush-ps-bridge/
# continues to count normally — it's live code.

# Legacy .NET Rush — top-level .cs files directly under dotnet/.
# Glob deliberately does NOT descend into subdirectories, so
# dotnet/rush-ps-bridge/*.cs still counts.
dotnet/*.cs     linguist-vendored
dotnet/*.sh     linguist-vendored
dotnet/*.csproj linguist-vendored

# Legacy .NET test project — entire subtree.
dotnet/Rush.Tests/** linguist-vendored
